# rethunk-git MCP (this workspace)

This project registers **rethunk-git** via [`.cursor/mcp.json`](.cursor/mcp.json) (local `bun src/server.ts`). Cursor supplies workspace roots at MCP initialize; do not rely on a fixed `cwd` in config.

**Full tool list, arguments, JSON shape, presets, and root-resolution order:** **[HUMANS.md](../../HUMANS.md)** and **[AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)**.

## When to use it

Prefer **`rethunk-git_git_*`** (and **`rethunk-git_list_presets`**) over shell **`git status`** / ad-hoc loops when describing multi-root or preset-driven git state. Resource **`rethunk-git://presets`** when the client supports MCP resources.

## When shell git is still fine

Commands the tools do not cover (e.g. `git diff`, `git cherry-pick`), or when MCP is unavailable after a failed reload.

If tools are missing: **reload MCP** or run **`bun install`** so `bun` resolves for `bun src/server.ts`.
